Locality: Gulf of Mexico, Florida, Port Manatee, approx 100 miles west
Comments: Conducted 10 annual pipeline inspections starting at Port Manatee going north to a depth of 200 feet, approx 100 miles offshore. Dozens of specimens observed from the port on the pipeline and rock piles covering the pipe near shore out to 22 miles. 100's of specimens on the bare pipe in the 135-207 ft. depth going out 100 miles off shore. Surveys were conducted over a 4 month period (June- September 2013).
